cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision techniques for removing rain from outdoor video footage, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves segmentation techniques (superpixel segmentation) and alignment of scene contents, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of neural networks and other machine learning techniques suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of fast camera motion, which is related to robotics (cs.RO).
